The executive Governor of Oyo state,  Governor Seyi Makinde has  appointed  Taiwo Adisa as his chief press secretary. Adisa until his appointment was the Group Politics Editor of Tribune Newspapers and the Abuja Bureau Chief of the media organisation. The appointment which takes immediate effect was confirmed in a statement made available to journalists in Ibadan by the Chief of Staff to the Governor, Chief Bisi Ilaka. Adisa, a shrewd journalist of repute had earlier served as Special Assistant (Media Relations) to former President of the Senate, Senator Adolphus Wabara between 2003 and May 2005. He was educated at the University of Ibadan, where he earned BA and MA degrees in Communication and Language Arts. His career in journalism spanned stints in The News Tempo Magazines, The Punch Newspapers and lately Tribune which he joined in July 2005. Apart from serving as the Group Politics Editor and Abuja Bureau Chief of Tribune, he also runs a weekly column in the Sunday Tribune called The Lynx-Eye, which he uses to dissect political developments across the country. Adisa who hails from Ogbomoso South local Government of the state is currently undertaking a Ph.D programme in Media Arts at the University of Abuja.